I am OK with the language because of the use of the word "appropriate" before 
"retail rate freezes".  However, in discussing this with Steven, it seems as 
if IEP has not yet put some guidance around "appropriate."  I would like to 
do so,  I suggest that IEP support a rate freeze solely for small customers 
-- if necessary -- and a similar rate freeze or even a shorter-term rate 
freeze for larger customers only as a last resort.  Do we need a call to 
discuss this?



